.TH "t4_memory_rw_init" 9 "t4_memory_rw_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4_memory_rw_init \- Get memory window relative offset, base, and size.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4_memory_rw_init
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "int win "  ","
.BI "int mtype "  ","
.BI "u32 *mem_off "  ","
.BI "u32 *mem_base "  ","
.BI "u32 *mem_aperture "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "win" 12
PCI-E Memory Window to use
.IP "mtype" 12
memory type: MEM_EDC0, MEM_EDC1, MEM_HMA or MEM_MC
.IP "mem_off" 12
memory relative offset with respect to \fImtype\fP.
.IP "mem_base" 12
configured memory base address.
.IP "mem_aperture" 12
configured memory window aperture.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Get the configured memory window's relative offset, base, and size.
